x4freetext: The data at 2.08 MeV
were used for normalization.  The absolute errors in
the cross sections were estimated to be about 15%.
A thin film of chemically pure silicon of natural
abundance 92.2% of Si-28 was thermally evaporated onto
a gold backing of 0.5-mg/cm**2 thickness and was then
covered by a thin gold layer in order to diminish the
target deterioration caused by the beam bombardment.
The thickness of the silicon film was about
The uncertainty of data normalization.
The the high limit of data uncertainties for
relative dependence of the cross sections on energy
originated mainly from the counting statistics  and  on
the evaluation of the area under peaks.

x4freetext: Measured cross section for O-16(d,p1) reaction at
857-KeV deuteron energy and 150 degree (5.3 +/- 0.4
mb/sr) was used for normalization.
A self-supporting Al(2)O(3)-film 60-mug/cm**2 thick
was used as a target. The thickness of the aluminium
range foil on the detector was 10-mum.
